JOHANNESBURG - New State Security Minister Bongani Bongo’s dealings while working for the Mpumalanga government have come back to haunt him. The Sunday Times reported new claims that Bongo received kickbacks from conveyancers of a government land deal in the province while he was heading legal services in the human settlements department. READ: Cabinet reshuffle: Meet the new minister A company belonging to his wife was allegedly paid R1.5-million, which the two are believed to have used to build a home in Nelspruit. The allegations come hot on the heels of claims the same conveyancers paid R300,000 towards the minister’s car. The allegations are still being investigated. eNCA